# Navigation snippets template reference

All navigation snippet methods are available under the `pt.snippets.navigation` template variable.

## Available methods

<div class="method-ref">
    
    <div class="method">
        <h3 class="method-title" id="snippets-nav-pagetree">pt.snippets.navigation.<span class="name">pageTree([startPage [, opts [, attrs ]]])</span></h3>
        <ul class="variables">
            <li><code>startPage</code>: <em>(optional)</em> Page to start generating the tree structure from. Defaults to homepage. Can be a <a href="{{ pt.pages.getUrlById('pages-order-ids') }}#assigning-ids">page ID</a> or a <a href="{{ pt.pages.getUrlById('template-ref-pages') }}#page-objects">page object</a>.</li>
            <li><code>opts</code>: <em>(optional)</em> Array of configuration options. See below for defaults.</li>
            <li><code>attrs</code>: <em>(optional)</em> Array of additional attributes to set on the opening list tag.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="method-desc">
            <p>Outputs a nested-list page tree structure, useful for generating navigation. The main nav for this documentation (on the left) is generated by it!</p>
        </div>
{% raw %}<pre class="brush: twig">{# Generate a full site page tree, current page is /index.php/about/bar #}
{{ pt.snippets.navigation.pageTree() }}
<ul>
    <li class="level-0 is-parent"><a href="/">Home</a>
        <ul>
            <li class="level-1 is-parent"><a href="/index.php/about">About</a>
                <ul>
                    <li class="level-2"><a href="/index.php/about/foo">Foo</a></li>
                    <li class="level-2 is-current"><a href="/index.php/about/bar">Bar</a></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="level-1"><a href="/index.php/contact">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul></pre>{% endraw %}
